Subset

calls.type <- calls.temp %>%
  group_by(type) %>%
  summarise(count = n()) %>%
  mutate(PCT = round(count/sum(count)*100,2))
calls <- subset(calls.temp, calls.temp$type == 'NOISE COMPLAINT')

Temporal Topologies

Day of Week and Hour of Day

Analysis:

During the days of the week and hour of the day map the hotpsots and coldspots stay pretty consistent. The hotspots are found on the weekends in a time frame of 11pm-2am. There are alot more complaints called in on the weekends because people are out and about with most people not having school or work the next day. The coldspots are also consistent across the book, the weekdays do not have as many noise complaints and every single day 3am-9pm there are limited if not no calls on noise complaints. This is the time of the day where people are out and about working or going to school, meaning no one is home. The noise complaints get higher as it gets later into the night and closer to the weekend, which is what is to be expected each week.

Day of Month and Month of Year

Analysis:

During the days of the month and month of the year map, there are more coldspots than hotspots. The main hotspots occur on July 3rd and 4th. On July 3rd and 4th people are setting off fireworks all night which a lot of people call in past a certain time. The cold spots are the majority of the days. This makes sense because the mean is 1 call a night and that’s what every day is and if there aren’t any calls then l there is none. In August there shouldn’t be much activity except for August 27th.

Month of Year and Year

Analysis:

During the month of the year and year map, the hotspots and coldspots are all scattered out. there is no specific pattern to them, except that the amount of noise complaints has gone down over the years. they have started to become more prominent during the summertime and around the wintertime. This would be due to kids not being in school as they enjoy summer or are on winter break. Within the next month of August, I expect the calls to start to come down due to kids settling in and getting ready for school.
